\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Standard
If the gold price goes to $2500, profit (before taxes and royalties etc)
 = $1300, which is profit up 26x! Stock up 10-20x!
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Check cash flows, reserves and potential production, leverage/costs, and
 react to special situations.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Gold miners have a big margin expansion and thus also volatility.
 Because if the mining costs would remain the same, and the price of gold
 is 1000 USD/ounce vs 2000 USD/ounce, then the margin would explode.
 The same is true in the opposite direction, when gold is cheaper.
 For example, mining costs = $1000 and the gold price is $1200, then the
 margin is $200.
 If the price of gold is $2000, then with the same mining costs, the margin
 would be $600, which is a three times more than it was previously - and
 the price of gold haven't even doubled.
\end_layout

